A man from Hrob "shot" his girlfriend from Kostomlat
The man from Hrob accidentally helped the officers to secure his countrywide wanted girlfriend from Kostomlat, who was wanted on an arrest warrant.
He called her himself.
He went about it in a roundabout way, however.
He first approached a passerby and made up a story that he had been robbed.
Officers responding to the 911 call arrived on the scene and couldn't believe their eyes when the alleged "victim" told them he made the whole thing up to get the officers to come to the scene.
In fact, he only wanted to ask the police officers for advice on how to file a report with the Czech Police.
After checking the identity of the man and his girlfriend, the officers discovered that the woman was on the national wanted list and a warrant for her arrest had been issued.
The case is therefore being handled by the Czech Police.
