The flame from Bethlehem is in the Czech Republic, the scouts took it from Austria
Břeclav - The flame that was lit in Bethlehem, where, according to Christian tradition, Jesus Christ was born, is in the Czech Republic.
However, the scouts did not go to Vienna due to the COVID-19 pandemic, and in the morning, they took him from their Austrian colleagues at the Reintal – Břeclav border crossing.
They took it from him at the border last year.
The Bethlehem Light is a beautiful Christmas tradition that we participate in every year with the department, and I look forward to it very much.
It is an honour for me to have been chosen, said scout Amálie Budíková to the journalists present.
While last year the handover took place at the Mikulov-Drasenhofen border crossing, directly on the border bridge, this year it will take place at the Reintal - Břeclav border crossing in the car park.
The scouts, however, usually travel by train to Vienna.
The distribution of the flame across the Czech Republic will remain the same.
The scouts traditionally set off with the Bethlehem light by train first to Brno, where they hand it over to the diocesan bishop Vojtěch Cikrle.
On Saturday, 18 December, scout couriers will deliver the lights on selected express and passenger trains.
The light will be taken over by local scouts or volunteers in stations, who will then spread the flame throughout the Czech Republic, even to places where there are no railways.
This year, too, scouts must comply with the current measures to prevent the spread of the coronavirus.
It is much the same as last year.
We are recommending both the delivery teams and the organizers of local events to of course wear face masks, try to keep their distance, be as few as possible, not to sing together, in other words, to behave in a way that is as safe as possible, described the spokesperson of the Betlémské světlo event, Zuzana Hrbková.
The tradition of the Bethlehem Light, which travels through Europe, was born in Austria in 1986.
The aim is to spread the idea of peace, friendship and harmony along with the flame.
For believers, the light of Bethlehem is a symbol of hope, a light that overcomes the darkness.
In the Czech Republic, the scouts and scouts have been taking care of its spread for more than 30 years.
Hundreds of volunteers make the event possible, and the flame is a symbol of selflessness and human solidarity.
All the news, including the list of places where people can get the flame, can be found on the website www.betlemskesvetlo.cz.
