From a legal point of view, Covid is on the list of infectious diseases.
That is to say, in the same group as HIV, the plague, yellow fever or typhus.
§ 152 Dissemination of a Contagious Human Disease
(1) Any person who intentionally causes or increases the risk of the introduction or spread of an infectious disease in humans shall be punished by imprisonment for a term of six months to three years, a fine or confiscation of property.
(2) A sentence of imprisonment for two years to eight years will be imposed on the offender,
(c) commits an act in breach of an important duty arising out of his employment, profession, position or function, or imposed on him by law, or
d) cause serious injury to health.
(3) A sentence of imprisonment for three to ten years shall be imposed on an offender who inflicts serious injury to the health of at least two persons or death as a result of the act referred to in paragraph 1.
(4) The perpetrator will be sentenced to a prison term of five to twelve years, if the act mentioned in subsection (1) results in the death of at least two persons.
