In May, she and her partner Russell Cox, 43, pleaded guilty to possession of cocaine with intent to supply.
She was found to have £1,600 worth of cocaine (about 50,000 Czech crowns) hidden in Kinder eggs in her home.
Cox was jailed for 30 months and Holland received a suspended sentence of 20 months.
