New timetables come into force in Prague on Sunday, mainly affecting commuter services
Passengers in Prague's integrated transport system (PID) can expect a number of changes from Sunday, mainly concerning suburban services.
New lines have been created, some have changed their routes, and others have ceased to exist.
Mladoboleslavsko is now joining the integrated system.
Since Sunday, the express trains from České Budějovice have stopped in Zahradní Město station in the capital.
The S7 suburban trains will run on the route from Beroun to Český Brod, passing through the Prague main station.
The recently opened station in Prague-Zahradní Město will now be served by the R17 express train from České Budějovice and Benešov.
The PID will be extended to other areas.
In addition, there will be buses to Světlá nad Sázavou, Blatná near Jesenice, Staré Splavy and Turnov.
Buses in the Mladá Boleslav region will be included, including lines with transfers to the Liberec and Hradec Králové regions.
In the course of the integration, 77 lines will be abolished, 37 new lines will be introduced and the operation of 12 existing lines will be adjusted.
A new bus line 405 will run from Prague's Zličín to Žatec.
A new direct connection between Prague and Kralovice near Rakovník has also been created, replacing the cancelled S53 train line.
The services from Prague to Rakovník will be strengthened in the morning rush hour and at the weekend, when the new express line number 404 will run.
The new lines included in the PID system are 400 and 410, which travel to the Liberec region.
They leave from the Střížkov metro station, not from the Holešovice railway station.
Bus line 400 runs through Mělník, Dubá and Česká Lípa to Nový Bor, and selected connections continue to Rumburk or Cvikov.
The supplementary line 410 runs via Mělník and Dubá to Doksy, Mimoň and Jablonné v Podještědí.
In contrast, the operation of dozens of local lines in central Bohemia has been cancelled or reduced, including to Mochov, Dobříš and Rožmitál pod Třemšínem.
All trains departing from Prague at 02:30 have been cancelled.
The long-term restrictions on the lines Prague – Beroun, Prague – Lysá nad Labem and in the vicinity of Kolín will continue due to the modernisation of the railway.
Travellers can expect changes at other places as well.
Buses are replacing some of the cancelled train lines or the section of the 420 line from Dobříš with a connection from Prague, where it is possible to use PID tickets all the way to Milevsko.
The routes of lines 540 to 543 in Nymbursko have been changed, and the routes of some buses on the border between Central Bohemia and Hořovicko in the Pilsen region have been adjusted.
